<TITLE> Sevilla swoop for Kone, Peurta honoured in Cup </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 SINGAPORE, Aug 31 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Soccer news in brief from around the world: Sevilla have spent a club record fee of 12 million euros ($16.40 million) on Ivory Coast striker Arouna Kone, who agreed to join the UEFA Cup holders on a five-year deal from PSV Eindhoven on Thursday. Kone's arrival means that Uruguayan striker Ernesto Chevanton is almost certain to be loaned out to another club this season. Sevilla players will wear shirts with Antonio Puerta's name on the back under their squad number during Friday's European Super Cup against AC Milan in honour of the 22-year-old who died on Tuesday, three days after collapsing in a league game against Getafe. English Premier League club Wigan Athletic have signed striker Marcus Bent on a season's loan from Charlton Athletic, who were relegated to the second division last season. Wigan is the 10th club of Bent's career
